Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
readDieAbstract(25.10)                                  readDieAbstract(25.10)

Name
       readDieAbstract - Reads the die abstract of the adjacent die

Syntax
       readDieAbstract

       <DIEABSTRACTFILE>

       Reads  the die abstract of the adjacent die. With this command, the ab-
       stract of the adjacent die is imported and  displayed  overlapped  with
       the current design.

       This command supports the embedded bump flow for hierarchical designs.

       The  readDieAbstract command is used after reading the stacked die con-
       fig file (XML) by using readTSVConfig because the die configuration  is
       required  for  die alignment.  You can turn off the import adjacent die
       objects by changing the visibility of abs* layers in the Custom tab  of
       the Color Preferences form.

Parameters
       <DIEABSTRACTFILE>
              Specifies the name of the die abstract file.

Examples
              * The following command reads a die abstract file die1.abs:

                readDieAbstract die1.abs

Related Information
              * readTSVConfig

              * writeDieAbstract

              * The  Color  Preferences section of the The Main Window chapter
                in Innovus Menu Reference.

